@X_Holyspawn_X2 @cryptocom Checked in with Crypto(dot)com support, they don't have any information on pursuing a BitLicense. I'm gonna guess they're not going to, and I honestly don't blame them. 

Just a frustrating situation to have to deal with for everyone
But yeah, man. This shit is infinitely frustrating.

Idk about Gemini. It took months for my account to get verified, so I quit paying attention to it when they never got back to me about the verification. 

Until one day out of the blue I got the "Your account has been verified!" email. 

Oh, cool.

I saw it with Doge, I saw it with Shib. 

Coinbase didn't start supporting them until after the initial blow up. None of us had a prayer at getting in until after it was already popular.

We have a choice of literally 2 exchanges; Coinbase & Gemini. 

And if there are coins that are not supported by one, the other, or both... Then we're just fucked, until they are.
I understand New York's want to make crypto safer for end users, but the BitLicense is absolutely stifling the entire crypto game here.
**Disclaimer: The following Tweets aren't geared toward just this single service, though. It's more about the crypto game in NY in general.
